<HEAD>Contras Claim To Down Soviet-Made Helicopter With Redeye Missile</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JOSE, Costa Rica (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Contra rebels claim they downed a
Soviet-made Sandinista air force helicopter in eastern Nicaragua
with a U.S.-made Redeye missile this week.
   The rebels, in a statement released in San Jose Friday, said
they used the heat-seeking anti-aircraft weapon last Sunday to
shoot down the MI-17 helicopter in Chontales province.
   In the Nicaraguan capital of Managua, a Defense Ministry
