children after viewing a rap video made in his honor by a
third-grade class.
   In their video, the third-graders at the Hallmark School rapped
that they and other Hallmark students ``don't have much money _ if
they could just see you, it would make their lives bright and
sunny.''
   The video was sent to Jackson at the Civic Center last week.
Teachers asked students to get permission slips signed by their
parents for a trip to the Civic Center but the youngsters weren't
told they were going to see Jackson until just before boarding
buses Thursday.
   ``It was good,'' said a smiling Kevin Morris, 6, before bein
spirited to the back of his bus by a woman who crisply said, ``We
can't talk to anybody.''
   Jackson ended nearly two weeks of secretive rehearsals Friday in
the Pensacola Civic Center for the tour scheduled to begin Tuesday
in Kansas City, Mo.
