<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Skunk Rescue,0148</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Motorist Rescues Injured Skunk, But No Animal Hospital Helps</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CONCORD, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A motorist whose heart was apparently
bigger than his nose rescued an injured skunk Saturday but could
not find an animal hospital to help, police said.
   The man, whom police declined to identify, found the animal off
Interstate 393 and bundled it into his car. He first took the skunk
to the Fish and Game Department, but no one was there, so he went
to the police, said Lt. James Fletcher.
   ``We couldn't find an animal hospital who would do something
with an injured skunk,'' he said. The animal apparently had been
hit by a vehicle and was badly injured, so police put it out of its
misery, Fletcher said.
   As for the good Samaritan, Fletcher said, the smell ``didn't
seem to bother him. I was a little surprised.''
