<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Earthquake-Colombia     02-20 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earthquake-Colombia,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Earthquake Shakes Central Colombia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake rattled central Colombia
Saturday evening, sending people in Bogota's high-rise apartments
and office buildings fleeing into the streets.
   There were no immediate reports of injuries from hospitals, fire
stations and police stations, according to the Colombian radio
network RCN.
   The tremor measured 5 on the Richter scale and the epicenter was
in the Andes about 50 miles south of Bogota, said the Geophysical
Institute of the Andes, according to RCN.
   The earthquake at 5:52 p.m. lasted three seconds and slight
aftershocks were registered 12 minutes later, a spokesman for the
Bogota institute said in the RCN report.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on
seismographs. Every increase of one number means a tenfold increase
in magnitude.
   An earthquake of 5 on the Richter scale can cause considerable
damage in the local area.
</TEXT>
