telephone are giving wrong answers even more often than a year ago,
when their accuracy rate was only 79 percent.
   Informal spot checks of the 4,500 IRS ``assistors'' found that
despite a concentrated effort by the agency to educate its
employees about the new law, the changes enacted in 1986 are so
far-reaching that one-third to one-half the answers to specific
